				<div class="talk-intro">
					<p id="tagline" class="notranslate">Batch to batch, crust to crust ... In tribute to the beloved staple food, baking master Peter Reinhart reflects on the cordial couplings (wheat and yeast, starch and heat) that give us our daily bread. Try not to eat a slice.</p>
											<p>
							Master breadmaker Peter Reinhart is also a teacher, author and theologian. Through his lectures and numerous cookbooks, he channels the science of baking into deep, spiritual lessons -- and dispels stale myths about the nature (and flavor) of good, wholesome bread. <a target="_blank" title="Peter Reinhart's bio" href="/speakers/peter_reinhart.html">Full bio </a>						</p>
					
											<div id="attributionText">
													</div>
									</div>

